      "Text": "systemd security update",
      "Title": "Synopsis",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for systemd is now available for openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP1,openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP2 and openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP3.",
      "Title": "Summary",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "System and Service Manager.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\nA flaw was found in systemd. An uncontrolled recursion in systemd-tmpfiles may lead to a denial of service at boot time when too many nested directories are created in /tmp.(CVE-2021-3997)",
      "Title": "Description",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for systemd is now available for openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP1,openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP2 and openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP3.\n\nopenEuler Security has rated this update as having a security impact of medium. A Common Vunlnerability Scoring System(CVSS)base score,which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVElink(s) in the References section.",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "Medium",
      "Title": "Severity",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "systemd",
      "Title": "Affected Component",
